de.boereck.matcher.eager

Class EagerMatcher

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.boereck.matcher.eager.EagerMatcher

  • public final class EagerMatcher
extends Object
    This class provides static methods to create matchers that can be used to perform checks on a given object or data type and perform an action if a check succeeds or when no check matched.

    All de.boereck.matcher implementations provided by methods of this class work eager, so all cases are evaluated one after the other (in the order they are specified) directly when the case methods are called. After a found, no further checks provided in from of predicates or functions are evaluated anymore. It is not needed to call a closing method on the provided CaseMatches, if no result is required.

    Advice: if you call methods to get/create Predicates or BooleanSuppliers for caseOf methods, better cache them in static fields where possible. This prevents creating the same objects over and over.

    This class is not intended to be instantiated or inherited from.

    • Method Detail

      • match

        public static <I> EagerNoResultCaseMatcher<I> match(I o)
        This method will return a EagerNoResultCaseMatcher object for the given input object. It allows definition of cases and associated actions. The cases will be evaluated eagerly when being defined and in order of their definition. After a matching case was found, no further case checks will be evaluated. Due to the eager evaluation it is not needed to use a closing method to start evaluation.
        Type Parameters:
        I - Type of match input object
        Parameters:
        o - object to find a matching case for
        Returns:
        CaseMatcher object to define cases on that will be checked immediately.

      • resultMatch

        public static <I,O> EagerResultCaseMatcher<I,O> resultMatch(I i)
        Returns a EagerResultCaseMatcher for the given input object. It allows definition of cases and associated functions, that will provide a value returned on closing methods. The cases will be evaluated eagerly when being defined and in order of their definition. After a matching case and therefore result value was found, no further case checks will be evaluated.
        Type Parameters:
        I - Type of match input object
        O - Type of output/result object of case matcher
        Parameters:
        i - object to find a matching case for
        Returns:
        CaseMatcher object to define cases on that will be checked immediately.

        public static <I,O> EagerResultCaseMatcher<I,O> resultMatch(Class<O> ouptutType,
                                                            I i)
        Returns a EagerResultCaseMatcher for the given input object. It allows definition of cases and associated functions, that will provide a value returned on closing methods. The type of the returned object can be defined by parameter outputType. The cases will be evaluated eagerly when being defined and in order of their definition. After a matching case and therefore result value was found, no further case checks will be evaluated.
